entries.body:
• Reports Q4 (Dec) earnings of $0.87 per share, excluding non-recurring items, $0.04 better than the FactSet Consensus of $0.83; revenues rose 7.9% year/year to $3.51 bln vs the $3.48 bln FactSet Consensus.
• Co issues in-line guidance for FY26, sees EPS of $2.85-3.15, excluding non-recurring items, vs. $2.99 FactSet Consensus.Organic revenue growth of 4% to 5%; Adjusted EBITDA of $930 million to $970 million; Adjusted diluted EPS2 of $2.85 to $3.15; and Adjusted EBITDA to free cash flow conversion of 30% to 40%
• Organic revenue growth of 4% to 5%;
• Adjusted EBITDA of $930 million to $970 million;
• Adjusted diluted EPS2 of $2.85 to $3.15; and
• Adjusted EBITDA to free cash flow conversion of 30% to 40%
